\begin_inset Formula \( xS_{n}=x+x^{2}+x^{3}+\cdots +x^{n-1}+x^{n} \)
\end_inset 

 and subtract to get 
\begin_inset Formula \( S_{n}-xS_{n}=1-x^{n} \)
\end_inset 

.
 Therefore we have
\begin_inset Formula \[
S_{n}=\frac{1-x^{n}}{1-x}\]

\end_inset 

Hence, if 
\begin_inset Formula \( |x|\, <\, 1 \)
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula \( x^{n}\rightarrow 0 \)
\end_inset 

 as 
\begin_inset Formula \( n\rightarrow \infty  \)
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Formula \( S_{n}\rightarrow \frac{1}{1-x} \)
\end_inset 

.
 In fact, 
\begin_inset Formula \( S_{n} \)
\end_inset 

 behaves like a power sequence
\begin_inset LatexCommand \index{power sequence}

\end_inset 

.
