\begin_inset Formula \( x\rightarrow 0^{+} \)
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula \( \ln (x)\rightarrow -\infty  \)
\end_inset 

.
 Hence at 
\begin_inset Formula \( x=0 \)
\end_inset 

 it seems appropriate that the series diverges to 
\begin_inset Formula \( -\infty  \)
\end_inset 

.
\layout Standard

